The Jigawa State Commissioner of Police CP Aliyu Sale Tafida has directed a thorough and clinical investigation into alleged extra-judicial killing by National Drug Law Enforcement Agency, NDLEA, officials. This was contained in a statement signed by the command spokesman ASP Lawan Shiisu Adam issued to DAILY POST. DAILY POST reported that the National Drugs Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) personnel have allegedly killed a 25-year-old man Murtala Gambo at Sundimina Village in Birnin Kudu local Government while on patrol. He said police and the agency have resolved to investigate into the circumstances surrounding his untimely death. He, therefore, advised residents to be law-abiding and stop taking law into their hands. He urged the law enforcement agencies to act in accordance with the Standard Operational Procedures (SOP) of the force and other extant laws guiding their overall conduct. Shiisu also called on sister security agencies to always report to the Divisional Police Officers before they embark on any operations.